      "id": "dc465612-2bbc-46be-ab1a-3eddd10b2161",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-04T02:28:37.107438+00:00",
      "type": "tool_result",
      "content": "```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"toolu_01GajLRaLFFVST5d78wRjeLo\",\n  \"name\": \"filesystem\",\n  \"content\": \"# Menai (AI Functional Programming Language)\\n\\nMenai is a pure functional programming language with Lisp-like S-expression syntax, designed\\nprimarily for use as an AI tool. It is homoiconic, strictly typed, and has no side effects,\\nmaking it safe for AI tool integration.\\n\\n> **Language reference**: Menai is designed to be used by AIs. The authoritative language\\n> reference is the AI tool description, which any AI assistant in this system can access\\n> directly. If you are a human user and want to know how a language feature works, just ask\\n> the AI.\\n\\n## Features\\n\\n- Pure functional: no side effects, immutable data\\n- Homoiconic: code and data share the same representation (S-expressions)\\n- Strict, runtime type system with no implicit coercion between numeric types\\n- Proper lists only (no cons cells or improper lists)\\n- Tail call optimization for recursive functions\\n- Pattern matching\\n- Dictionaries with O(1) lookup\\n- Module system\\n- Trace debugging support\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\nMenai uses an optimizing compiler pipeline feeding into a bytecode VM:\\n\\n```text\\nSource code\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiLexer                \\u2013 tokenization\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiASTBuilder           \\u2013 S-expression parsing to AST (MenaiASTNode)\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiASTSemanticAnalyzer  \\u2013 type checking, scope analysis, free variable detection\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiASTModuleResolver    \\u2013 resolve and inline imports (recursive module compilation)\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiASTDesugarer         \\u2013 expand syntactic sugar (let, let*, letrec, quote, etc.)\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiASTConstantFolder    \\u2013 constant folding optimization pass\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiIRBuilder            \\u2013 lower AST to IR (MenaiIRNode)\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiIROptimizer          \\u2013 IR-level dead binding elimination (fixed-point loop)\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiCFGBuilder           \\u2013 lower IR to SSA control-flow graph (MenaiCFGFunction)\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiCFG passes           \\u2013 CollapsePhiChains, BranchConstProp, SimplifyBlocks\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiVCodeBuilder         \\u2013 lower CFG to linear VCode (phi-free, virtual registers)\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiBytecodeBuilder      \\u2013 slot allocation, peephole optimisation, emit CodeObject\\n    \\u2502\\n    \\u25bc\\nMenaiVM                   \\u2013 register-based bytecode virtual machine\\n```\\n\\nModules are resolved and cached before optimization passes run, allowing\\ncross-module optimizations.\\n\\n## Implementation\\n\\n- Python 3.10+, no external dependencies\\n- All runtime values are immutable frozen dataclasses (`MenaiValue` hierarchy)\\n- Lists are backed by Python tuples\\n- Alists use a tuple of pairs with a hash-backed dict for O(1) lookup\\n- Tail calls are detected during compilation and optimized in the VM\\n\\n## Python API\\n\\n### Basic usage\\n\\n```python\\nfrom menai import Menai\\n\\ntool = Menai()\\nresult = tool.evaluate(\\\"(integer+ 1 2 3)\\\")  # Returns: MenaiValue\\n```\\n\\n### Configuration\\n\\n```python\\ntool = Menai(\\n    max_depth=200,                          # Maximum call stack depth\\n    module_path=[\\\".\\\", \\\"menai_modules\\\"],     # Module search path\\n)\\n```\\n\\n### Module management\\n\\n```python\\ntool.clear_module_cache()                   # Clear cached modules\\ntool.set_module_path([\\\".\\\", \\\"my_modules\\\"])   # Update search path (clears cache)\\n```\\n\\n### Trace watchers\\n\\n```python\\nfrom menai import MenaiStdoutTraceWatcher, MenaiBufferingTraceWatcher\\n\\n# Print traces to stdout\\ntool = Menai()\\ntool.add_trace_watcher(MenaiStdoutTraceWatcher())\\n\\n# Collect traces into a buffer\\nwatcher = MenaiBufferingTraceWatcher()\\ntool.add_trace_watcher(watcher)\\ntool.evaluate(\\\"...\\\")\\nprint(watcher.get_traces())\\n```\\n\\n### Error handling\\n\\n```python\\nfrom menai import Menai, MenaiError, MenaiParseError, MenaiEvalError\\n\\ntool = Menai()\\ntry:\\n    result = tool.evaluate(\\\"(integer+ 1 2\\\")\\nexcept MenaiParseError as e:\\n    print(f\\\"Parse error: {e}\\\")\\nexcept MenaiEvalError as e:\\n    print(f\\\"Eval error: {e}\\\")\\nexcept MenaiError as e:\\n    print(f\\\"Menai error: {e}\\\")\\n```\\n\\n### Value types\\n\\nRuntime values are instances of the `MenaiValue` hierarchy:\\n\\n| Class           | Menai type  |\\n|-----------------|-------------|\\n| `MenaiInteger`  | `integer`   |\\n| `MenaiFloat`    | `float`     |\\n| `MenaiComplex`  | `complex`   |\\n| `MenaiString`   | `string`    |\\n| `MenaiBoolean`  | `boolean`   |\\n| `MenaiSymbol`   | `symbol`    |\\n| `MenaiList`     | `list`      |\\n| `MenaiDict`     | `dict`      |\\n| `MenaiSet`      | `set`       |\\n| `MenaiFunction` | `function`  |\\n\\n## Module system\\n\\nModules are `.menai` files containing a single expression that evaluates to a value\\n(typically an dict of exported functions). They are imported with `(import \\\"module-name\\\")`.\\n\\n## Development tools\\n\\nThe `tools/` directory contains utilities for working with Menai:\\n\\n- `menai_benchmark/` \\u2013 performance benchmarking\\n- `menai_bytecode_analyzer/` \\u2013 bytecode inspection\\n- `menai_checker/` \\u2013 static analysis\\n- `menai_disassembler/` \\u2013 bytecode disassembly\\n- `menai_pretty_print/` \\u2013 code formatting\\n\",\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n`content` is:\n```markdown\n# Menai (AI Functional Programming Language)\n\nMenai is a pure functional programming language with Lisp-like S-expression syntax, designed\nprimarily for use as an AI tool. It is homoiconic, strictly typed, and has no side effects,\nmaking it safe for AI tool integration.\n\n> **Language reference**: Menai is designed to be used by AIs. The authoritative language\n> reference is the AI tool description, which any AI assistant in this system can access\n> directly. If you are a human user and want to know how a language feature works, just ask\n> the AI.\n\n## Features\n\n- Pure functional: no side effects, immutable data\n- Homoiconic: code and data share the same representation (S-expressions)\n- Strict, runtime type system with no implicit coercion between numeric types\n- Proper lists only (no cons cells or improper lists)\n- Tail call optimization for recursive functions\n- Pattern matching\n- Dictionaries with O(1) lookup\n- Module system\n- Trace debugging support\n\n## Architecture\n\nMenai uses an optimizing compiler pipeline feeding into a bytecode VM:\n\n```text\nSource code\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiLexer                \u2013 tokenization\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiASTBuilder           \u2013 S-expression parsing to AST (MenaiASTNode)\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiASTSemanticAnalyzer  \u2013 type checking, scope analysis, free variable detection\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiASTModuleResolver    \u2013 resolve and inline imports (recursive module compilation)\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiASTDesugarer         \u2013 expand syntactic sugar (let, let*, letrec, quote, etc.)\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiASTConstantFolder    \u2013 constant folding optimization pass\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiIRBuilder            \u2013 lower AST to IR (MenaiIRNode)\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiIROptimizer          \u2013 IR-level dead binding elimination (fixed-point loop)\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiCFGBuilder           \u2013 lower IR to SSA control-flow graph (MenaiCFGFunction)\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiCFG passes           \u2013 CollapsePhiChains, BranchConstProp, SimplifyBlocks\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiVCodeBuilder         \u2013 lower CFG to linear VCode (phi-free, virtual registers)\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiBytecodeBuilder      \u2013 slot allocation, peephole optimisation, emit CodeObject\n    \u2502\n    \u25bc\nMenaiVM                   \u2013 register-based bytecode virtual machine\n```\n\nModules are resolved and cached before optimization passes run, allowing\ncross-module optimizations.\n\n## Implementation\n\n- Python 3.10+, no external dependencies\n- All runtime values are immutable frozen dataclasses (`MenaiValue` hierarchy)\n- Lists are backed by Python tuples\n- Alists use a tuple of pairs with a hash-backed dict for O(1) lookup\n- Tail calls are detected during compilation and optimized in the VM\n\n## Python API\n\n### Basic usage\n\n```python\nfrom menai import Menai\n\ntool = Menai()\nresult = tool.evaluate(\"(integer+ 1 2 3)\")  # Returns: MenaiValue\n```\n\n### Configuration\n\n```python\ntool = Menai(\n    max_depth=200,                          # Maximum call stack depth\n    module_path=[\".\", \"menai_modules\"],     # Module search path\n)\n```\n\n### Module management\n\n```python\ntool.clear_module_cache()                   # Clear cached modules\ntool.set_module_path([\".\", \"my_modules\"])   # Update search path (clears cache)\n```\n\n### Trace watchers\n\n```python\nfrom menai import MenaiStdoutTraceWatcher, MenaiBufferingTraceWatcher\n\n# Print traces to stdout\ntool = Menai()\ntool.add_trace_watcher(MenaiStdoutTraceWatcher())\n\n# Collect traces into a buffer\nwatcher = MenaiBufferingTraceWatcher()\ntool.add_trace_watcher(watcher)\ntool.evaluate(\"...\")\nprint(watcher.get_traces())\n```\n\n### Error handling\n\n```python\nfrom menai import Menai, MenaiError, MenaiParseError, MenaiEvalError\n\ntool = Menai()\ntry:\n    result = tool.evaluate(\"(integer+ 1 2\")\nexcept MenaiParseError as e:\n    print(f\"Parse error: {e}\")\nexcept MenaiEvalError as e:\n    print(f\"Eval error: {e}\")\nexcept MenaiError as e:\n    print(f\"Menai error: {e}\")\n```\n\n### Value types\n\nRuntime values are instances of the `MenaiValue` hierarchy:\n\n| Class           | Menai type  |\n|-----------------|-------------|\n| `MenaiInteger`  | `integer`   |\n| `MenaiFloat`    | `float`     |\n| `MenaiComplex`  | `complex`   |\n| `MenaiString`   | `string`    |\n| `MenaiBoolean`  | `boolean`   |\n| `MenaiSymbol`   | `symbol`    |\n| `MenaiList`     | `list`      |\n| `MenaiDict`     | `dict`      |\n| `MenaiSet`      | `set`       |\n| `MenaiFunction` | `function`  |\n\n## Module system\n\nModules are `.menai` files containing a single expression that evaluates to a value\n(typically an dict of exported functions). They are imported with `(import \"module-name\")`.\n\n## Development tools\n\nThe `tools/` directory contains utilities for working with Menai:\n\n- `menai_benchmark/` \u2013 performance benchmarking\n- `menai_bytecode_analyzer/` \u2013 bytecode inspection\n- `menai_checker/` \u2013 static analysis\n- `menai_disassembler/` \u2013 bytecode disassembly\n- `menai_pretty_print/` \u2013 code formatting\n\n```",
      "completed": true,
