      "content": "```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"toolu_01RwPakHECLogd2DkTPP8iWJ\",\n  \"name\": \"filesystem\",\n  \"content\": \"# AGENTS.md \\u2014 tools/menai\\n\\nDeveloper tools for working with Menai source files and bytecode. Each tool is\\na standalone Python script that adds `src/` to its own path, so all can be run\\nfrom any working directory.\\n\\nFor invocation details (flags, options, examples) read the tool's own source\\nfile or its README where one exists.\\n\\n## benchmark \\u2014 `benchmark/run.py`\\n\\nCompares Menai performance against idiomatic Python and pure-functional Python\\nacross a set of algorithmic benchmark suites.\\n\\nEach suite benchmarks three implementations of the same algorithm: Menai (run\\non the Menai VM), idiomatic Python (using mutation and built-ins), and\\nfunctional Python (pure-functional style matching Menai's semantics). The\\nfirst implementation (Menai) is the reference; all others are validated against\\nit with per-suite correctness checks. Timing is reported as mean and minimum\\nwall-clock time in milliseconds, with a speedup/slowdown ratio relative to the\\nreference.\\n\\n## checker \\u2014 `checker/check.py`\\n\\nValidates parenthesis balance in a `.menai` file. Uses the Menai lexer so that\\nparentheses inside strings and comments are correctly ignored.\\n\\nProduces a line-by-line depth chart and identifies the exact location of any\\nimbalance. Closing parentheses can optionally be annotated with the special\\nform they close (`lambda`, `let`, `letrec`, `if`, `match`). Supports ANSI\\ncolour output with depth-matched colouring on parentheses, line numbers, and\\nannotations. Exit codes are suitable for CI/CD use.\\n\\n## disassembler \\u2014 `disassembler/disassemble.py`\\n\\nCompiles a `.menai` file and prints annotated bytecode for every `CodeObject`\\nin the module, recursing into nested closures.\\n\\nEach function section lists its code-objects table, constants table, input\\nparameters, captured free variables, and an annotated instruction listing.\\nInstructions are annotated with what they load, call, or close over. Jump\\ntargets are marked and control-flow boundaries are visually separated. An\\noptional call-trace mode summarises which functions call which.\\n\\n## pretty-print \\u2014 `pretty-print/pretty-print.py`\\n\\nFormats Menai source code using `MenaiPrettyPrinter` from `src/menai`. Reads\\nfrom a file or stdin and writes to stdout, a file, or back in-place.\\n\\nShort expressions are kept on one line; longer ones are broken across lines\\nwith consistent indentation. `lambda`, `if`, `match`, `let`, `let*`, and\\n`letrec` receive special multi-line layouts with aligned bindings. End-of-line\\nand standalone comments are preserved. A check mode (exit 0/1) is available\\nfor use in pre-commit hooks or CI.\\n\\n## profiler \\u2014 `profiler/profile.py`\\n\\nCompiles and executes a `.menai` file under Python's `cProfile`, then prints a\\nsummary of the hottest call sites. Prelude compilation happens before profiling\\nstarts and is excluded from the results, so the profile reflects only the user\\nprogram's execution cost.\\n\\nRaw profile data can optionally be saved to a `.prof` file for further\\ninspection with `pstats` or `snakeviz`. Benchmark programs are in\\n`tests/` (e.g. `sudoku-solver.menai`, `rubiks_cube.menai`, `list-sort.menai`).\\n\\n## test-runner \\u2014 `test-runner/test-run.py`\\n\\nDiscovers `*_test.menai` files, parses their test trees, and executes each\\nleaf thunk in an isolated VM invocation. A runtime error in one test does not\\naffect any other.\\n\\nTest files export a dict with a `\\\"tests\\\"` key containing a node-list \\u2014 a\\nnested structure of named groups (branches) and zero-argument lambdas (leaves).\\nThe runner reports pass/fail per leaf with the full group path, and exits with\\na non-zero code if any test fails. An optional name filter runs only the tests\\nwhose path contains a given substring.\\n\\nThe `menai_test` support module (`test-runner/menai_test.menai`) is injected by the\\nrunner and provides `assert-equal` (polymorphic structural equality check) and\\nthe internal `test-find` navigation helper. It is not part of the standard\\n`menai_modules/` library.\\n\",\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n`content` is:\n```markdown\n# AGENTS.md \u2014 tools/menai\n\nDeveloper tools for working with Menai source files and bytecode. Each tool is\na standalone Python script that adds `src/` to its own path, so all can be run\nfrom any working directory.\n\nFor invocation details (flags, options, examples) read the tool's own source\nfile or its README where one exists.\n\n## benchmark \u2014 `benchmark/run.py`\n\nCompares Menai performance against idiomatic Python and pure-functional Python\nacross a set of algorithmic benchmark suites.\n\nEach suite benchmarks three implementations of the same algorithm: Menai (run\non the Menai VM), idiomatic Python (using mutation and built-ins), and\nfunctional Python (pure-functional style matching Menai's semantics). The\nfirst implementation (Menai) is the reference; all others are validated against\nit with per-suite correctness checks. Timing is reported as mean and minimum\nwall-clock time in milliseconds, with a speedup/slowdown ratio relative to the\nreference.\n\n## checker \u2014 `checker/check.py`\n\nValidates parenthesis balance in a `.menai` file. Uses the Menai lexer so that\nparentheses inside strings and comments are correctly ignored.\n\nProduces a line-by-line depth chart and identifies the exact location of any\nimbalance. Closing parentheses can optionally be annotated with the special\nform they close (`lambda`, `let`, `letrec`, `if`, `match`). Supports ANSI\ncolour output with depth-matched colouring on parentheses, line numbers, and\nannotations. Exit codes are suitable for CI/CD use.\n\n## disassembler \u2014 `disassembler/disassemble.py`\n\nCompiles a `.menai` file and prints annotated bytecode for every `CodeObject`\nin the module, recursing into nested closures.\n\nEach function section lists its code-objects table, constants table, input\nparameters, captured free variables, and an annotated instruction listing.\nInstructions are annotated with what they load, call, or close over. Jump\ntargets are marked and control-flow boundaries are visually separated. An\noptional call-trace mode summarises which functions call which.\n\n## pretty-print \u2014 `pretty-print/pretty-print.py`\n\nFormats Menai source code using `MenaiPrettyPrinter` from `src/menai`. Reads\nfrom a file or stdin and writes to stdout, a file, or back in-place.\n\nShort expressions are kept on one line; longer ones are broken across lines\nwith consistent indentation. `lambda`, `if`, `match`, `let`, `let*`, and\n`letrec` receive special multi-line layouts with aligned bindings. End-of-line\nand standalone comments are preserved. A check mode (exit 0/1) is available\nfor use in pre-commit hooks or CI.\n\n## profiler \u2014 `profiler/profile.py`\n\nCompiles and executes a `.menai` file under Python's `cProfile`, then prints a\nsummary of the hottest call sites. Prelude compilation happens before profiling\nstarts and is excluded from the results, so the profile reflects only the user\nprogram's execution cost.\n\nRaw profile data can optionally be saved to a `.prof` file for further\ninspection with `pstats` or `snakeviz`. Benchmark programs are in\n`tests/` (e.g. `sudoku-solver.menai`, `rubiks_cube.menai`, `list-sort.menai`).\n\n## test-runner \u2014 `test-runner/test-run.py`\n\nDiscovers `*_test.menai` files, parses their test trees, and executes each\nleaf thunk in an isolated VM invocation. A runtime error in one test does not\naffect any other.\n\nTest files export a dict with a `\"tests\"` key containing a node-list \u2014 a\nnested structure of named groups (branches) and zero-argument lambdas (leaves).\nThe runner reports pass/fail per leaf with the full group path, and exits with\na non-zero code if any test fails. An optional name filter runs only the tests\nwhose path contains a given substring.\n\nThe `menai_test` support module (`test-runner/menai_test.menai`) is injected by the\nrunner and provides `assert-equal` (polymorphic structural equality check) and\nthe internal `test-find` navigation helper. It is not part of the standard\n`menai_modules/` library.\n\n```",
