      "tool_call_context": "`expression` is:\n```menai\n; Simulate a \"harness\" that injects file content as `input-text`,\n; then runs a PURE Menai transform: renumber an ordered list so the\n; numbers are sequential, leaving non-list lines untouched.\n(let ((input-text \"Shopping list:\\n3. apples\\n7. bananas\\n1. cherries\\nNotes:\\n9. (ignore me, I'm prose)\\n2. dates\"))\n  (letrec\n    ((digit? (lambda (c) (and (string>=? c \"0\") (string<=? c \"9\"))))\n     (count-digits\n       (lambda (chars n)\n         (if (list-null? chars)\n             n\n             (if (digit? (list-first chars))\n                 (count-digits (list-rest chars) (integer+ n 1))\n                 n))))\n     (renumber\n       (lambda (lines counter)\n         (if (list-null? lines)\n             ()\n             (let* ((line (list-first lines))\n                    (d (count-digits (string->list line) 0)))\n               (if (and (integer>? d 0)\n                        (string=? (string-slice line d (integer+ d 2)) \". \"))\n                   (list-prepend\n                     (renumber (list-rest lines) (integer+ counter 1))\n                     (string-concat (integer->string counter) \". \"\n                                    (string-slice line (integer+ d 2))))\n                   (list-prepend\n                     (renumber (list-rest lines) counter)\n                     line)))))))\n    (list->string (renumber (string->list input-text \"\\n\") 1) \"\\n\")))\n```"
